    {
      "text": "Raiden II (雷電II, Raiden Tsū) is a 1993 vertically scrolling shooter arcade video game developed and published by Seibu Kaihatsu. It is the second game in the Raiden series which started with Raiden in 1990.\nRaiden II was ported to Windows by Kinesoft and Microsoft Corporation. The Windows version uses Red Book audio for music. This game and the original Raiden were released for the PlayStation as The Raiden Project.",
